cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL

The paper proposes a deep neural architecture trained by using expectation learning for unsupervised learning tasks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep learning architectures (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) for crossmodal stimuli association. The paper also mentions the enhancement of generalization and adaptation in dynamic environments, which suggests that it may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the processing of crossmodal stimuli, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-category.
